<br>
Anyrate, that said, this isn't the only board that gimpzor is making personal attacks on. <br>
<br>
I think Reign's idea has merit. Set aside a few hours one week, and post it as a &quot;hunt time&quot; like a scheduled raid, complete with sign up.  Set a start time, and an end time, and IF folks sign up, then they are comitting to being online during those hours, and perhaps get a weighted roll as result (200-1200, instead of 1 1000 or something). This is in no way &quot;elite&quot; or &quot;uber&quot; so it shouldn't piss anyone off - and if someone happens to just be on during that time, they still have a pretty good shot at loot. <br>
<br>
I don't like points systems either. To me, they are just dumb. I've heard the justification, well x could really use that, and he has been to the last 49 raids. Where Z won the item, and he attends like one raid every 6 months, and plays maybe 2 hours a week, which he usually spends soloing in zone y. So what? How is that unfair? <br>
<br>
BUT, for everyone's consideration, here is how a guild on FV works its point system. I don't endorse this, its just an FYI post. This guild (Ebon Storm) is a lower mid rank guild - its not in the category of Legion of Little Folk,but would be above some of the smaller guilds in the Federation (it is bigger than my FV guild, which is Indigo Void).<br>
<br>
_______________________________________<br>
Loot Rules<br>
<br>
All loot will be obtained via the point system. We feel this is the most fair and equitable way for everyone. The people who put the most into will get the most out of it.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Point Breakdown-<br>
<br>
1 point being on time ( 10 min window of designated raid start time )<br>
1 point for attending the raid<br>
1 point for staying until raid completion<br>
<br>
2 points for puller. Each raid will have primary puller if he/she should leave during raid secondary puller will also receive points. Pulling is an important job and we want to accommodate our pullers.<br>
The pulling duty may be volunteered for but the Senior Officers/Guild leader will appoint the most qualified candidate.<br>
<br>
Epic Battles – 1 point per group required for the battle.<br>
<br>
8 points for Gods, dragons, 60+ mobs ( this is for all in attendance )<br>
<br>
*This is a rough diagram of how points assigned. The GL will designate point value for each raid.<br>
*points will be tracked by Senior officer/Guild leader and will be on display.<br>
*poor conduct/form on raid will result in loss or no points.<br>
<br>
<br>
Gems-<br>
<br>
Gems obtained on guild raids will be utilized as follows- <br>
Blue Diamonds, Diamonds, Jaciniths will be collected by Senior officer.<br>
A list will be kept of what resistant gears are needed. Resist gear will be made<br>
the person receiving it needs to cover cost of the metal.<br>
Resist Gear Priority- 1- Melees<br>
2- Clerics<br>
3- Chanters<br>
4- Other Casters<br>
Feel free to get your own resist gear as well. This prioritization is to maximize efficiency on raids<br>
<br>
Cash Loot/Non-Resist Gems<br>
Black Sapphires, ruby crowns ect…. Will be collected and given to clerics to cover buff costs and necros if summon corpses are needed.<br>
<br>
Using Points-<br>
<br>
The auction system will only be used in “high end” encounters. i.e. dragon loot, ultra rare loot.<br>
Even though points will continue accumulate they will only be used towards high end gear.<br>
The Guild Leader/Sr Officer will let everyone know before raid if this qualifies as “high end encounter”.<br>
If not loot will be distributed via dice system on NBG “need before greed”.<br>
Everyone gets an item via dice system before you may roll for 2nd item in your class.<br>
<br>
All items will be briefly announced so you know what is up for grabs.<br>
The auctioneer will announce what classes are able to bid on the said item.<br>
Once you bid the item you may not turn it back in if you win. It yours enjoy!<br>
If there comes a time when an item is not desired by anyone or useable by anyone ( ie pally book off Vox) it will become guild property and sold for Gem/coffin fund.<br>
Max Bid Value- whatever the auctioneer deems as the “starting bid”. The item shall not exceed 3x that value.<br>
If the items reaches the bid “cap” and there are several people willing to spend the max value points on it.<br>
The winner shall be decided in the following order criteria:<br>
1- raid attendance&lt; history &gt; if tie,<br>
2- level , if still tie,<br>
3- person with better loot will win and will be expected to pass down old loot to tied player and the old item will cost the person points &lt; GL will decide point value of handed down loot&gt;<br>
<br>
Example- Mage Planar robe drops and opening bid is 10 points. 2 mages are willing to bid max bid which would be 30 points. So the mage who has most historied raid points &lt; current and used&gt; would get it. If that was a tie the higher leveled mage would get it. If it was still a tie the mage with better armor would get it under the pretense they have to pass the old armor down. If they don’t want to the other mage has the option to take it and has to pass down armor if it is an upgrade for the other mage. The pass down loot will be assigned a point value as well and will be charged to the person receiving it.<br>
<br>
<br>
If you were not in the raid you may not bid on any item from that raid.<br>
Non classes can not bid on item. IE caster bidding on haste item for melee.<br>
Points may not be pooled with other people.<br>
<br>
Buy Back Items-<br>
If a item that is worth high value and is deemed to stay in guild. It will be announced that this is a buy back. Once said member out grows this Item ES will buy it back for 50-75% point value depending on the item value at buyback time. This is not optional.<br>
<br>
Epics-<br>
<br>
Epic pieces will not be under normal loot rules. If we are after an epic piece for you and we obtain the item it is yours. This will be stated before raid starts.<br>
If several people need a said epic item from a raid the Guild Leader will consult the message board to see who is the furthest. If you have not filled out message board you will not be considered. If several people are at the same point the Guild leader will deem who gets it based on raid attendance and tenure in the guild. This is not negotiable.<br>
Amendment to this-<br>
How Epic Loot will be handled-<br>
Based on:<br>
<br>
*Who is furthest on their epic ( based on information in Epic Endeavors) if tie then,<br>
*Raid Attendance ( Totaled points used/remaining ) if tie still then,<br>
*Higher Level<br>
<br>
Epic raids will be given priority by their usefulness to guild. i.e. clerics and chanter also<br>
how far along you are will have some bearing as well.<br>
Epic encounters are very time consuming and more often than not the loot is sub standard.<br>
The Senior officers/Guild Leader will monitor epic raids and make sure we do not burn ourselves out<br>
on them. Moderation is a good thing. Everyone gets excited as they get closer to completion but we must maintain a balance.<br>
Also epic raids will be given priority to those who attend raids. If you do not attend raids and expect<br>
Epic raids for your benefit you are sadly mistaken. This is a team effort not an individual effort.<br>
Epic raids will be cleared through via Guild Leader and/or Senior officers. They shall base decisions upon guild participation ex. Attendance at guild raids.<br>
<br>
If you are planning an epic raid you will be expected to know the in and outs.<br>
• Zone layout<br>
• How many people needed to successfully complete it<br>
• Time required<br>
• Cost incurred gems/coffins/port stones<br>
• Mob level, stats, what resistances needed<br>
<br>
