<br>
The Federation has always dealt with loot on a NEED BEFORE GREED basis.  This will NEVER change, or I simply won't participate, as I am sure many others won't as well.  This is not even a debateable topic, and people shouldn't have concerns over it.<br>
<br>
What Reign is suggesting is that we have gotten to the point where many of the zones we had to plan WELL in advance for, are now nearly &quot;trivial&quot; to the majority of our players, because we have done them so often and most everyone is familiar with the encounters.<br>
<br>
In order for many of us to advance further, not only in terms of LOOT, (which this conversation was never really about) but in terms of challenge and something new to accomplish.  We have proven in the past that we are very capable of taking down mobs as powerful as Zelnithak, Radiir, Tawtro, Talendor, Ragefire, Treah, Servitor, etc...etc...etc.  However, these mobs aren't there at our leisure, we need to coordinate tracking of them in order to take advantage of the opportunity when they spawn.<br>
<br>
We won't ever stop doing planned raids.  However, it is certainly within our best interests to be ready on a whim to mobilize and do something unique and exciting like take down a boss mob.<br>
<br>
I would like to see us create a list of mobs people would like to track, and see who is willing to park a tracker there to check on the spawns from time to time.  This is all voluntary, of course, but it can only benefit us by improving our ability to coordinate mobilization, improve communication, and provide better entertainment than killing the same mobs over and over until we get the lewtz we want.<br>
<br>
P.S. - Posting annonymous is cowardly and shallow, as was illustrated by Gimpzor who felt no need to use logic to back up his/her points, and turned his/her post into a mindless rant.  I don't care how much you disagree with someone posting on this board, that fact entitles you in no way to start a flame war and use harsh language, and doing so SHOULD get you banned.<br>
<br>
We really NEED to be respectful of each other for this Federation to work.  Projecting fear, blame, shame, frustration and animosity on the board does nobody any good and really takes the fun out of what is meant to be a forum of friends sharing ideas and inspiration. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000080><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ucompboy484.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CompBoy484</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Soldier of the Federation</span><br>  Posts: 102<br> <font color=#70DB93>(9/8/02 5:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=348.topic&index=37>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.eq-darklegion.com/images/Oumphoto2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Get a grip.</span><hr size=1> Am already working on a Venril Sathir mule (don't know what level I should get him to be able to track him, though.) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000060><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ufilumtil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Filumtil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Soldier of the Federation</span><br>  Posts: 162<br> <font color=#70DB93>(9/9/02 12:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=348.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.camelot.de/~ekraemer/filumtil3.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Get a grip.</span><hr size=1> Well said, Ravilicus.<br>
